1
00:00:09,250 --> 00:00:11,166
[NARRATOR]
Shangri-la.

2
00:00:13,708 --> 00:00:16,583
[NARRATOR] A land where
harmony exists side-by-side

3
00:00:16,666 --> 00:00:19,000
with chaos, science with magic,

4
00:00:19,083 --> 00:00:21,708
and human beings with demons.

5
00:00:21,791 --> 00:00:25,666
Alas, the delicate age-old
balance has begun to erode.

6
00:00:25,750 --> 00:00:28,416
A dark aura encroaches
from the West,

7
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:30,291
sowing evil in its wake.

8
00:00:30,375 --> 00:00:33,833
The soil has withered,
demons have turned violent,

9
00:00:33,916 --> 00:00:37,000
human beings live in fear.

10
00:00:37,083 --> 00:00:40,083
A utopia, once upheld
by the twin pillars

11
00:00:40,166 --> 00:00:42,333
of Faith and Civilization,

12
00:00:42,416 --> 00:00:47,166
lay in ruins, swallowed
whole by darkness.

13
00:01:00,708 --> 00:01:02,500
[gasps]

14
00:01:02,583 --> 00:01:03,333
[DONKEY whinnies]

15
00:01:03,416 --> 00:01:05,333
[gasping]

16
00:01:05,416 --> 00:01:07,250
They're behind us! Hurry!

17
00:01:08,583 --> 00:01:09,750
[MAN 1A yelps]

18
00:01:13,666 --> 00:01:16,416
[DEMON 1A] We were tryin'
to be covert, but no,

19
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:18,875
you just had to notice us.

20
00:01:18,958 --> 00:01:20,000
Is it me,

21
00:01:20,083 --> 00:01:23,041
or do humans seem
paranoid these days?

22
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:25,625
Don't you give me that look!

23
00:01:25,708 --> 00:01:27,541
Where does a filthy
animal like you get off

24
00:01:27,625 --> 00:01:29,875
snarling your teeth at us?

25
00:01:29,958 --> 00:01:31,458
[gasps]

26
00:01:31,541 --> 00:01:32,875
What's it gonna be?

27
00:01:32,958 --> 00:01:35,750
Wanna die like your buddy here?
Or d'you fancy a deal?

28
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:37,958
Your life in exchange
for showing us the rock

29
00:01:38,041 --> 00:01:39,458
your village is hiding under?

30
00:01:39,541 --> 00:01:41,333
Go! Run for it!

31
00:01:41,416 --> 00:01:43,416
[panting]

32
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:47,375
I see. Right then.
Suit yourself.

33
00:01:47,458 --> 00:01:49,166
Death it is.

34
00:01:49,250 --> 00:01:50,666
[DEMON 1C yells]

35
00:01:53,625 --> 00:01:55,125
[RANDOM DEMON 1A groans]

36
00:01:57,916 --> 00:02:00,166
[DEMONS gasp]

37
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,666
[DEMON 1E] What the--?
Where'd these guys come from?

38
00:02:09,750 --> 00:02:11,375
Get out of our way!

39
00:02:11,458 --> 00:02:13,541
[SANZO]
You talkin' to us?

40
00:02:13,625 --> 00:02:15,875
You're the assholes
blockin' the road.

41
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,375
[RANDOM DEMON 1C]
Oh, shit.

42
00:02:20,458 --> 00:02:23,250
[DEMONS groaning]

43
00:02:27,083 --> 00:02:28,791
[yells]

44
00:02:30,041 --> 00:02:32,666
[DEMONS groaning]

45
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:34,791
C'mon! Let's go!

46
00:02:41,041 --> 00:02:46,166
How? Wait? Who are you?

47
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:36,125
[stomachs growling]

48
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:37,625
[TAMURO'S FATHER]
Uh...

49
00:04:37,708 --> 00:04:39,125
[MAN 1A]
Okay.

50
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:52,958
[MAN 1B]
Damn it. What's wrong with you?

51
00:04:53,041 --> 00:04:55,125
Why would you bring
outsiders here?

52
00:04:55,208 --> 00:04:58,416
Have you two idiots forgotten
the position we're in?

53
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,125
I didn't have a choice.

54
00:05:00,208 --> 00:05:02,375
They saved our lives. I had to!

55
00:05:02,458 --> 00:05:03,875
Our donkey was
killed in the fight

56
00:05:03,958 --> 00:05:05,000
and these men were good enough

57
00:05:05,083 --> 00:05:06,958
to let us load our
things in their car.

58
00:05:07,041 --> 00:05:11,083
[WOMAN 1A] But, they look
so seedy. How old are they?

59
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:13,250
[MAN 1D] Word has it some
great priest is heading out

60
00:05:13,333 --> 00:05:15,250
West to slaughter demons.

61
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:17,166
Could be they have
something to do with him.

62
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:18,375
[WOMAN 1B]
You're talking about the one

63
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:20,000
they call Sanzo, right?

64
00:05:20,083 --> 00:05:23,125
I mean, I hear he travels
with a entourage,

65
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:24,500
but aren't they supposed
to be the picture

66
00:05:24,583 --> 00:05:25,750
of nobility and grace?

67
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:26,958
[MAN 1B]
Who cares?

68
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:28,708
Can we focus on clearing
out of here, please?

69
00:05:28,791 --> 00:05:31,750
It's only a matter of time
before the demons find us.

70
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:33,208
--[gasps]
--[MAN 1C] Exactly!

71
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:38,791
[snoring]

72
00:05:38,875 --> 00:05:42,625
[TAMURO] That smell.
Is it from being on the road?

73
00:05:43,875 --> 00:05:45,541
They reek.

74
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:49,375
[HAKKAI]
Terribly sorry.

75
00:05:49,458 --> 00:05:51,625
You were kind enough to feed
a group of total strangers,

76
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:53,375
and we fall asleep.

77
00:05:53,458 --> 00:05:54,833
[GOJYO]
I can't remember the last time

78
00:05:54,916 --> 00:05:57,666
we had a proper meal,
let alone a decent nap.

79
00:05:57,750 --> 00:06:01,250
[TAMURO] It's fine.
You guys saved my dad, so...

80
00:06:02,458 --> 00:06:03,750
Where'd you come from?

81
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:05,708
[HAKKAI]
Chang'an.

82
00:06:05,791 --> 00:06:06,666
[TAMURO]
Chang'an?

83
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:09,083
Way out East. Quite the place.

84
00:06:09,166 --> 00:06:11,916
Biggest, liveliest city
in all of Shangri-la.

85
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,833
Nowhere quite like it.

86
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:18,541
Surprised you managed
to get this far in one piece.

87
00:06:18,625 --> 00:06:20,958
Whew. Yeah, 's been
pretty rough this time.

88
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:22,666
I thought I was
a goner for sure.

89
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,583
Hah! From what? Starving?

90
00:06:24,666 --> 00:06:27,666
You've survived a helluva
lot worse than this.

91
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,416
I'm gonna have me a bath.

92
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,958
But, we've imposed
on them quite enough.

93
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:33,250
[TAMURO]
It's no trouble.

94
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:35,541
The adults may not
like it, though.

95
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:37,958
You're probably all right
if you can stay quiet.

96
00:06:38,041 --> 00:06:40,583
If you make too much
noise, they beat you.

97
00:06:40,666 --> 00:06:42,041
See? We're in trouble now!

98
00:06:42,125 --> 00:06:43,916
Yeah? So why are you blaming me?

99
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:47,416
Ah, guess they prefer things
on the peaceful side.

100
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:50,583
Seems a little tucked away, too.

101
00:06:50,666 --> 00:06:52,958
Not many villages around here.

102
00:06:53,041 --> 00:06:55,416
Populated ones, at least.

103
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:58,541
The few we saw looked
like they'd been raided.

104
00:06:58,625 --> 00:07:00,333
[TAMURO] Most of folks
cleared out of this region

105
00:07:00,416 --> 00:07:01,875
a while back.

106
00:07:01,958 --> 00:07:03,416
[GOJYO]
Huh. Now that you mention it,

107
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:06,125
we have been running into
a lot of demons lately.

108
00:07:06,208 --> 00:07:07,208
[GOKU]
Gee, ya think?

109
00:07:07,291 --> 00:07:09,791
'S why my clothes
are all torn up.

110
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:12,000
[TAMURO]
Remember the drawbridge

111
00:07:12,083 --> 00:07:14,125
you crossed to get here?

112
00:07:14,208 --> 00:07:17,000
We only use it when
we absolutely have to.

113
00:07:17,083 --> 00:07:21,625
Demons would've found us
ages ago if we left it open.

114
00:07:21,708 --> 00:07:23,500
Still, though...

115
00:07:23,583 --> 00:07:25,500
[TAMURO'S FATHER]
Damn shame.

116
00:07:25,583 --> 00:07:28,000
As you can see,
we tend to be suspicious

117
00:07:28,083 --> 00:07:30,291
of outsiders nowadays.

118
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:31,750
Been living in fear so long,

119
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:33,958
we've forgotten how
to be hospitable.

120
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:36,916
Hardly turn a light on
once the sun goes down.

121
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,666
It's a modest place, sure,

122
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:41,791
but we were cheerful
once upon a time.

123
00:07:41,875 --> 00:07:44,750
I'm sure you were.

124
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,833
It's fine, We won't
get comfortable.

125
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:49,541
We have some business
to attend to.

126
00:07:49,625 --> 00:07:51,333
Yes, well. Uh.

127
00:07:51,416 --> 00:07:53,750
In any event, I'm afraid
I have to ask you gents

128
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:56,416
to stay with us
till tomorrow morning.

129
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:58,541
And why is that?

130
00:07:58,625 --> 00:08:00,125
[TAMURO'S FATHER]
We only let the drawbridge down

131
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:02,541
at sunup and dusk. I'm sorry.

132
00:08:02,625 --> 00:08:05,583
We just can't risk
demons getting in.

133
00:08:05,666 --> 00:08:08,750
[TAMURO] Dad. They'd like
a bath, if that's okay.

134
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:11,500
[TAMURO'S FATHER] Ah. S'pose
you could use one, eh?

135
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:13,000
Be my guest.

136
00:08:13,083 --> 00:08:15,000
[HAKKAI] I suggest we
split off into pairs.

137
00:08:15,083 --> 00:08:16,291
Whoa. Hold on a sec.

138
00:08:16,375 --> 00:08:17,833
So, I finally get to take a bath

139
00:08:17,916 --> 00:08:19,666
and you're saying it has
to be with one of you?

140
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,250
[SANZO]
I'm bathing it alone.

141
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:22,500
You three knock yourselves out.

142
00:08:22,583 --> 00:08:23,333
What?

143
00:08:23,416 --> 00:08:25,458
How do we pick who's first?

144
00:08:25,541 --> 00:08:26,708
Rock-paper-scissors?

145
00:08:26,791 --> 00:08:27,625
[GOJYO, SANZO]
Hey.

146
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:29,875
[HAKKAI]
Ready? One, two, three!

147
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:34,750
[GOKU]
Ah! This feels amazing!

148
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:37,750
'Least they have hot water,
even if I have to share it

149
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:39,083
Huh. Look at this.

150
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:41,125
Hakkai should cut my hair.

151
00:08:41,208 --> 00:08:43,833
Jeez. Gotta say, this
place is a lot different

152
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:44,833
than what I'm used to.

153
00:08:44,916 --> 00:08:45,958
Hey! Cheer up!

154
00:08:46,041 --> 00:08:47,916
At least the food's
delicious, right?

155
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,916
Ugh. Is that really
all you ever notice?

156
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,083
[GOKU]
What'd you expect?

157
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:52,916
We're in the western
part of Shangri-la.

158
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,541
Things are supposed
to be different.

159
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:57,291
Speaking of which,
how much further to India?

160
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:59,000
[thud]

161
00:08:59,083 --> 00:09:01,416
[WOMAN screams]

162
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:03,666
[GOJYO, GOKU scream]

163
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:05,125
What's the matter with you?

164
00:09:05,208 --> 00:09:08,083
Uh, they asked us to be
quite if you recall.

165
00:09:08,166 --> 00:09:10,083
Help! There was a ghost!

166
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:11,208
What?

167
00:09:11,291 --> 00:09:15,208
There! She was at
the window! I swear!

168
00:09:15,291 --> 00:09:18,375
[REI] ♪ The peaches
grow so brightly. ♪

169
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:22,291
♪ So flavorful and
strong standing there, ♪

170
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:25,541
♪ underneath all
the tall trees. ♪

171
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:28,583
--♪ Sweetly longing for... ♪
--Her name's Rei.

172
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:32,625
She hasn't always been
like that. Her husband died.

173
00:09:32,708 --> 00:09:35,250
We basically treat her
like a nuisance now.

174
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:36,791
[MAN 1D] What have we you
told you about singing?

175
00:09:36,875 --> 00:09:38,833
[RANDOM MAN 1C]
You have to be silent!

176
00:09:38,916 --> 00:09:41,125
[TAMURO] The thing about
her husband, though...

177
00:09:41,208 --> 00:09:44,583
He didn't just die--
he was murdered!

178
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:47,166
Demons attacked him on the road.

179
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:48,958
He was on his way back
from a supply run,

180
00:09:49,041 --> 00:09:50,583
just like my dad.

181
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:53,583
Talk about being between
a rock and hard place.

182
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:55,666
He was so close to the village.

183
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:58,708
When they attacked, he led 'em
straight to the drawbridge.

184
00:09:58,791 --> 00:09:59,750
We all heard.

185
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:01,750
We all knew he was in trouble,

186
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:03,750
but do ya think we
lowered it for him?

187
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:04,833
'Course not.

188
00:10:04,916 --> 00:10:06,750
Well, can't say I blame them.

189
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:09,916
If they'd given him a chance,
he might still be alive today!

190
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,000
We're monsters!

191
00:10:11,083 --> 00:10:14,416
We sacrificed one
of our own people!

192
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:19,541
This place. I hate it with
ever fiber of my being.

193
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:28,916
[HAKKAI] That's the anger
talking. He doesn't mean it.

194
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:33,666
Deep down, he understands
the demons are responsible.

195
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:35,916
[SANZO]
Hey. Put some clothes on.

196
00:10:37,875 --> 00:10:39,333
[SANZO]
You're scaring the locals.

197
00:10:39,416 --> 00:10:40,958
Are those men naked?

198
00:10:41,041 --> 00:10:43,041
We were fools to let them in.

199
00:10:43,125 --> 00:10:45,541
--[GOKU] Uh...
--[GOJYO] My bad.

200
00:10:45,625 --> 00:10:48,791
[REI]
♪ In the shadows, he wait-- ♪

201
00:10:48,875 --> 00:10:50,791
[MAN 1D]
I told you to stop singing!

202
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:53,041
Darling, please!
Don't be so harsh!

203
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:54,166
We have to be silent!

204
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:56,416
It's the only way to survive!

205
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:59,583
The demons find this place,
that'll be it for us!

206
00:10:59,666 --> 00:11:01,708
Do forgive me, Rei.

207
00:11:01,791 --> 00:11:06,000
I feel for you, honestly,
but we're all suffering here.

208
00:11:06,083 --> 00:11:07,708
Her husband was a damn fool.

209
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:10,583
Tamuro's father made it
back alive, didn't he?

210
00:11:11,916 --> 00:11:14,750
[MAN 1D] What's done is
done. It was him or us.

211
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,291
[GOKU]
An actual futon!

212
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:22,958
Yeah, sorry the
room's so cramped,

213
00:11:23,041 --> 00:11:24,166
but it's all we've got.

214
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:25,666
There's nothing
to apologize for.

215
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:26,916
[GOJYO]
Think fast!

216
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,291
Hey, four walls, a ceiling
and a nice futon?

217
00:11:29,375 --> 00:11:31,250
What else could we need?

218
00:11:31,333 --> 00:11:34,333
I'll make certain my friends
settle down presently.

219
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:36,708
Thanks. Get a good night's rest.

220
00:11:36,791 --> 00:11:39,125
See you boys bright n' early.

221
00:11:39,208 --> 00:11:42,708
Thank you again, sir.
Good night.

222
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:46,250
[GOJYO] He-He-Hey! Flashy bit
o' craftsmanship, huh?

223
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:47,416
You could say that,

224
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:49,833
though I believe a
better word is exotic.

225
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:52,166
We may still be within
the borders of Shangri-la,

226
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:54,958
but this region is
a world unto itself.

227
00:11:55,041 --> 00:11:56,125
[SANZO]
Yeah.

228
00:11:56,208 --> 00:11:58,291
Goes to show how far
West we've traveled.

229
00:11:58,375 --> 00:12:00,875
The dark aura's influence
around here is strong.

230
00:12:00,958 --> 00:12:02,958
The sheer number of demons
we keep running into

231
00:12:03,041 --> 00:12:05,000
in these parts is
all the proof I need.

232
00:12:05,083 --> 00:12:06,875
Feels as though we're
behind enemy lines,

233
00:12:06,958 --> 00:12:08,625
fighting for our lives.

234
00:12:08,708 --> 00:12:10,333
So, I'm guessin' this is
your way of telling us

235
00:12:10,416 --> 00:12:11,791
to prepare ourselves.

236
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:13,875
Thank you, but,
given things lately,

237
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:15,958
we kinda get the point.

238
00:12:16,041 --> 00:12:18,166
[GOKU]
Seriously, though. I'm stoked!

239
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:20,708
Everything's so different here,
it's hard not to be!

240
00:12:20,791 --> 00:12:22,708
It's like we're on
a journey for real!

241
00:12:22,791 --> 00:12:24,375
[SANZO] What the hell
are you talking about?

242
00:12:24,458 --> 00:12:26,333
We've been on the
road for two years.

243
00:12:26,416 --> 00:12:28,750
Being a monkey sure
does have it perks.

244
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:31,583
The water they use here
doesn't agree with me.

245
00:12:31,666 --> 00:12:33,916
Yeah, you don't wear
diarrhea sprite very well.

246
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,458
I'm not a diarrhea sprite!

247
00:12:35,541 --> 00:12:38,333
I have a sensitive
stomach! Shut up!

248
00:12:38,416 --> 00:12:39,791
Okay. Settle down.

249
00:12:39,875 --> 00:12:42,166
We have an early day tomorrow.

250
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:44,291
Anybody who oversleeps
gets left behind.

251
00:12:44,375 --> 00:12:45,500
[GOJYO]
Oh, come on!

252
00:12:45,583 --> 00:12:46,708
Don't spread out like
you're the only one

253
00:12:46,791 --> 00:12:49,000
with futon privileges!
You're not a king.

254
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:51,375
[SANZO]
No. I'm Sanzo.

255
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:52,541
[GOJYO]
Wow.

256
00:12:52,625 --> 00:12:56,000
[REI] ♪ The peaches
grow so brightly. ♪

257
00:12:56,083 --> 00:13:01,250
♪ So flavorful and strong
standing there, ♪

258
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:03,833
♪ underneath all
the tall trees. ♪

259
00:13:03,916 --> 00:13:07,791
♪ Sweetly longing for our song ♪

260
00:13:07,875 --> 00:13:11,333
♪ Who do I spy,
standing there, ♪

261
00:13:11,416 --> 00:13:13,041
♪ In the sha-- ♪

262
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:18,125
--[TOWNSPEOPLE screaming]
--[crashing]

263
00:13:18,208 --> 00:13:19,916
[RANDOM MAN 1A]
Help!

264
00:13:24,958 --> 00:13:26,791
[ROOSTER crows]

265
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:31,208
[MAN groans]

266
00:13:31,291 --> 00:13:33,166
No, they're here!

267
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,791
[gasps]

268
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,291
[RANDOM DEMON 1K] I see you
in there! C'mon, open up!

269
00:13:38,375 --> 00:13:39,416
Who the hell is that?

270
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:40,791
We're in big trouble!

271
00:13:40,875 --> 00:13:42,875
Demons have overrun the village!

272
00:13:42,958 --> 00:13:44,000
[TAMURO'S FATHER]
What?

273
00:13:48,583 --> 00:13:49,708
Weird.

274
00:13:49,791 --> 00:13:51,875
I could've sworn this
door opened inwards.

275
00:13:54,916 --> 00:13:57,166
[GOJYO] You're disturbing
my beauty rest!

276
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:58,208
This way, please.

277
00:13:58,291 --> 00:13:59,958
[yelling]

278
00:14:01,625 --> 00:14:02,458
[GOKU yells]

279
00:14:02,541 --> 00:14:04,250
[DEMON 1M groans]

280
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:06,750
What the...? Who're they?

281
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,416
Just some guys you've
woken up two hours too soon.

282
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:15,041
You maggots have no idea
the bloodbath you're in for.

283
00:14:17,208 --> 00:14:19,250
[DEMON 1S]
Pure white robes.

284
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:21,333
Silver pistol.

285
00:14:21,416 --> 00:14:23,625
Intensely purple eyes.

286
00:14:23,708 --> 00:14:24,916
Golden hair.

287
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,166
Oh, no.

288
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:30,583
Attended by three
demon-like followers!

289
00:14:30,666 --> 00:14:33,541
Could... Could it
possibly be...?

290
00:14:38,416 --> 00:14:41,958
[DEMON 1S]
The Genzo Sanzo Party?

291
00:14:42,041 --> 00:14:43,708
They come from the East.

292
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:45,291
Wherever they go,

293
00:14:45,375 --> 00:14:47,500
it is said mountains
of demon corpses

294
00:14:47,583 --> 00:14:50,250
darken the sky in their wake.

295
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:54,250
They're the most ruthless band
of outlaws in all of Shangri-la!

296
00:14:56,791 --> 00:14:58,833
It's them! We're
totally screwed!

297
00:14:58,916 --> 00:15:00,708
Ah! No! It's not possible!

298
00:15:00,791 --> 00:15:01,958
They vanished ages ago!

299
00:15:02,041 --> 00:15:04,125
Last I heard, they're
supposed to be dead!

300
00:15:04,208 --> 00:15:06,041
That's kind of a
rude thing to say.

301
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:07,541
Well, damn.

302
00:15:07,625 --> 00:15:09,208
Ya know, I thought it was
strange none of these lowlifes

303
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:11,625
were cursing our name
while we slaughtered them.

304
00:15:11,708 --> 00:15:13,583
We are rather filthy.

305
00:15:13,666 --> 00:15:15,291
It's difficult to
recognize anyone beneath

306
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:18,125
so many layers of dirt,
or so I imagine.

307
00:15:18,208 --> 00:15:19,250
You're kidding, right?

308
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:22,000
[REI]
♪ ...peaches grow so brightly. ♪

309
00:15:22,083 --> 00:15:24,750
♪ So flavorful and strong... ♪

310
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:27,250
Easy, fellas.
Put down your weapon.

311
00:15:27,333 --> 00:15:28,958
Fun's over.

312
00:15:29,041 --> 00:15:31,125
Somebody help her!

313
00:15:31,208 --> 00:15:33,916
[DEMON 1H] One false move
and the songbird gets it.

314
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,791
Something tells me a
holy man wouldn't want

315
00:15:35,875 --> 00:15:38,791
a woman's death
on his conscience.

316
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:39,750
Ugh.

317
00:15:39,833 --> 00:15:41,000
Again?

318
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:43,041
How many times have we
been in this situation?

319
00:15:43,125 --> 00:15:44,083
Well, there you have it.

320
00:15:44,166 --> 00:15:45,625
Villains are always
true to form.

321
00:15:45,708 --> 00:15:47,458
I'll say that much for them.

322
00:15:47,541 --> 00:15:49,208
[DEMON 1H laughs]
Well, whaddya know?

323
00:15:49,291 --> 00:15:51,458
I had a feeling this crazy
bitch would come in handy

324
00:15:51,541 --> 00:15:54,250
if I let her live
long enough. All right!

325
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:55,666
Enough with the singing!

326
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:56,958
Let go of her!

327
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:58,583
[WOMAN 1E]
Tamuro! Don't!

328
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,166
Is that it?

329
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:02,500
We stand around like last time
and watch one of our own die?!

330
00:16:02,583 --> 00:16:04,291
[MAN 1F]
What choice do we have?

331
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:06,958
She reaps what she sows, kid.

332
00:16:07,041 --> 00:16:08,458
Far as I'm concerned,
it's her fault

333
00:16:08,541 --> 00:16:10,083
the demons got here
in the first place.

334
00:16:10,166 --> 00:16:11,083
To hell with her!

335
00:16:11,166 --> 00:16:12,708
[TAMURO growls]

336
00:16:12,791 --> 00:16:14,583
What is wrong with you?!

337
00:16:14,666 --> 00:16:16,458
Don't you know
what she's singing?

338
00:16:16,541 --> 00:16:17,833
Listen to her!

339
00:16:17,916 --> 00:16:20,791
She's not just spouting off
some random nonsense!

340
00:16:20,875 --> 00:16:26,125
[REI] ♪ For so long, the tree
stood so proud and strong ♪

341
00:16:26,208 --> 00:16:27,208
♪ as the proudest man... ♪

342
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:29,208
[TAMURO'S FATHER]
The festival.

343
00:16:29,291 --> 00:16:33,041
She's singing our festival song!

344
00:16:33,125 --> 00:16:36,583
[TAMURO] Every last one of us
lives in fear of demons.

345
00:16:36,666 --> 00:16:38,125
Rei's no different.

346
00:16:38,208 --> 00:16:41,750
Her grief just drove her to
madness. But still, here she is.

347
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:45,666
Passing our song
on to the children.

348
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:47,291
She's still in there!

349
00:16:47,375 --> 00:16:50,041
Some part of her doesn't
want it to be forgotten.

350
00:16:50,125 --> 00:16:52,583
Some part of her
looks to the future,

351
00:16:52,666 --> 00:16:56,750
to a time when--when we can
sing like in the old days.

352
00:17:01,375 --> 00:17:02,958
[TAMURO'S FATHER]
I'm sorry.

353
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:06,750
It's wrong of us
to cast her off.

354
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:10,541
We were all just so
focused on getting by.

355
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:14,625
What becomes of a village
when it forgets its own song?

356
00:17:14,708 --> 00:17:20,041
When its children can't play,
or its people laugh?

357
00:17:20,125 --> 00:17:21,958
[SANZO] Look, none of
this really has anything

358
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:24,166
to do with us,
but we do owe you one.

359
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:26,458
Hospitality goes
a long way, after all.

360
00:17:26,541 --> 00:17:28,666
If you want us to do
something, say the word.

361
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:31,541
[DEMONS panting]

362
00:17:31,625 --> 00:17:33,541
Ugh, poor thing.

363
00:17:33,625 --> 00:17:35,541
I... I was dead wrong.

364
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:39,000
Bring her back!
Save Rei, I'm begging you!

365
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:41,375
[DEMONS groan]

366
00:17:43,375 --> 00:17:45,166
[SANZO]
There's a lesson here, I think.

367
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:47,791
Wherever you go, whoever
you're dealing with.

368
00:17:47,875 --> 00:17:49,750
Look close enough and
you'll see that, deep down,

369
00:17:49,833 --> 00:17:51,875
the same hearts beats
in all of us.

370
00:17:51,958 --> 00:17:56,333
[GOJYO] Ha! Nice. Couldn't've
said it better myself.

371
00:17:56,416 --> 00:18:00,583
The more things change, the
more they stay the same, huh?

372
00:18:03,666 --> 00:18:05,416
We've got a problem
on our hands, people!

373
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:06,541
The two demons that got away

374
00:18:06,625 --> 00:18:08,208
are making a break
for the drawbridge!

375
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:09,583
They'll get away!

376
00:18:09,666 --> 00:18:11,625
We can't let them
walk out of here!

377
00:18:11,708 --> 00:18:13,541
Oh, god! If they bring
back reinforcements,

378
00:18:13,625 --> 00:18:14,875
we're done for!

379
00:18:14,958 --> 00:18:17,333
All the other demons will
know where to find us!

380
00:18:17,416 --> 00:18:18,750
[gasps] Hakuryu!

381
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:20,416
[HAKURYU chirps]

382
00:18:22,791 --> 00:18:24,291
Welp. Thanks for the grub!

383
00:18:24,375 --> 00:18:26,291
Oh, and the futon!

384
00:18:26,375 --> 00:18:28,083
Sorry to duck out
unceremoniously,

385
00:18:28,166 --> 00:18:29,666
but time is of the essence.

386
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:30,791
Oh, don't worry.

387
00:18:30,875 --> 00:18:32,875
We'll take care of the runaways.

388
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:34,708
It's the least we could do.

389
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:42,791
There goes an odd bunch.

390
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:44,458
Who'd they say they were again?

391
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:46,875
Oh, yeah. I dunno.

392
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:50,750
Let's call 'em The Squall.

393
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:52,541
[DEMONS panting]

394
00:18:52,625 --> 00:18:54,291
[DEMON 1AC]
You've gotta be shittin' me!

395
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:56,166
We don't stand a chance
against those guys!

396
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:57,166
They're unreal!

397
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:58,583
[engine revs]

398
00:18:58,666 --> 00:18:59,916
[DEMON 1AC gasps]

399
00:19:01,291 --> 00:19:03,416
--[screams]
--Son of a--!

400
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:05,791
[DEMON 1AC]
Go! We can make it!

401
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:10,208
[DEMON 1AD] Let's see
the bastards catch us now!

402
00:19:10,291 --> 00:19:11,666
Good luck!

403
00:19:13,375 --> 00:19:14,916
Brace yourselves!

404
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:23,875
[DEMONS scream]

405
00:19:25,083 --> 00:19:26,791
[GOKU] ♪ The peaches
grow so brightly. ♪

406
00:19:26,875 --> 00:19:29,791
♪ Flavorful and strong ♪

407
00:19:29,875 --> 00:19:31,291
♪ Blooming sweetly
in the orchard... ♪

408
00:19:31,375 --> 00:19:33,541
[GOJYO]
♪ Blooming sweetly. ♪

409
00:19:33,625 --> 00:19:35,041
[BOTH] ♪ Who do I spy,
standing there, ♪

410
00:19:35,125 --> 00:19:36,083
♪ beneath the
tallest tree-- ♪

411
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:37,625
[SANZO]
Stop singing.

412
00:19:37,708 --> 00:19:40,333
[HAKKAI] To be fair, that tune
does get suck in your head.

413
00:19:40,416 --> 00:19:42,500
[SANZO]
Which I why I asked you to stop!

414
00:19:42,583 --> 00:19:45,541
[GOKU] Ow! You never
let us have any fun!

415
00:19:45,625 --> 00:19:48,208
[GOJYO] Like I said,
the more things change...

416
00:19:48,291 --> 00:19:49,708
Anyone else feel like
we're stuck in a loop?

417
00:19:49,791 --> 00:19:53,083
[HAKKAI laughs]
That's one way of looking at it.

418
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:57,125
What you call a loop some people
might refer to as our style.

419
00:20:01,083 --> 00:20:04,500
So, uh, the sun
rises in the East.

420
00:20:04,583 --> 00:20:08,416
Just like you predicted,
Talche. Nice one.

421
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,541
[TALCHE]
The stars do not lie.

422
00:20:14,708 --> 00:20:16,375
The sun's path is eternal.

423
00:20:16,458 --> 00:20:19,166
Forever and ever unchanging.

424
00:20:19,250 --> 00:20:22,250
It rises in the East. Always.

425
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:25,541
Then sinks Westward.

426
00:20:25,625 --> 00:20:27,750
To Earth.

427
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:32,291
It falls and the land
is engulfed in darkness.

428
00:20:33,791 --> 00:20:37,250
Is that another one
of your prophesies?

429
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:40,666
Nay. Providence.

430
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:15,125
[SANZO]
Episode Two: "Cloud Mirror."

431
00:22:15,208 --> 00:22:17,125
Don't miss it.

432
00:22:17,208 --> 00:22:20,500
[GOJYO, GOKU, HAKKAI, SANZO]
Ready, and Ura Sai!

433
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,000
[singing fevtival tune]

434
00:22:24,083 --> 00:22:25,750
Okay. Star Festival, huh?

435
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,708
Its exceedingly hard
to keep proper track

436
00:22:27,791 --> 00:22:30,041
of what day it is when
you're out on the open road.

437
00:22:30,125 --> 00:22:31,958
We mustn't lose sight of
the bigger picture here,

438
00:22:32,041 --> 00:22:33,291
wouldn't you agree?

439
00:22:33,375 --> 00:22:36,041
[GOJYO] "I wanna eat all
the meat buns." Shocking.

440
00:22:36,125 --> 00:22:37,666
Does everything have
to be about food?

441
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:39,208
[GOKU]
Maybe! So what?

442
00:22:39,291 --> 00:22:42,125
I noticed you wrote the word
"debauchery" on yours, Sanzo.

443
00:22:42,208 --> 00:22:43,208
Wry as ever.

444
00:22:43,291 --> 00:22:44,833
Every man wants that. Shut up.

445
00:22:44,916 --> 00:22:46,916
Cheap dream if you ask me.

446
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,958
[GOKU]
Hm? How come Gojyo gets two?

447
00:22:49,041 --> 00:22:50,208
I didn't write that, I swear.

448
00:22:50,291 --> 00:22:52,833
[SANZO] Give us a break.
Who the hell else would?

449
00:22:52,916 --> 00:22:55,333
[GOKU] Mm. Wait.
I take it back. This is...

450
00:22:55,416 --> 00:22:56,458
--[car horn honks]
--[HAKURYU chirps]

451
00:22:56,541 --> 00:22:58,166
[GOJYO, GOKU, HAKKAI, SANZO]
Ura Sai.

452
00:22:58,250 --> 00:23:01,875
[GOKU singing festival tune]

453
00:23:03,166 --> 00:23:04,500
[GOKU]
Where's yours, Sanzo?

454
00:23:04,583 --> 00:23:05,875
If you can't
get it for yourself,

455
00:23:05,958 --> 00:23:07,333
what's the point of wishing?

456
00:23:07,416 --> 00:23:08,458
Stubborn as usual.

457
00:23:08,541 --> 00:23:10,416
Let me just write
one for you, then.

458
00:23:10,500 --> 00:23:13,041
"I wish my male
pattern baldness--"

459
00:23:13,125 --> 00:23:16,708
[GOKU singing festival tune]

